# Money Scam Detector (Burmese) — MLOps Showcase

An end-to-end system for classifying Burmese scam messages using mmdt-tokenizer preprocessing, classical ML models, MLflow tracking, FastAPI serving, and Streamlit UI.

```
money-scam-mm/
├── configs/ (train/mlflow/inference/thresholds)
├── src/moneyscam/ (features, models, pipeline, serving)
├── ui/streamlit_app.py
├── tests/ (unit + API stubs)
├── Dockerfile.api, docker-compose.yml
└── reports/, models/, data/
```

## Quickstart
- Install deps: `uv pip install -r requirements.txt -r requirements-dev.txt`
- Train (classical): `uv run python -m moneyscam.pipeline.train_classical --config configs/train.yaml`
- Run API: `uv run uvicorn moneyscam.serving.api:app --reload`
- Run Streamlit UI: `uv run streamlit run ui/streamlit_app.py`

## Experiment Tracking (MLflow)
- Configure `configs/mlflow.yaml` or `.env` (`MLFLOW_TRACKING_URI`, `MLFLOW_EXPERIMENT_NAME`).
- Each run logs params, CV metrics, test metrics, confusion matrix, metrics.json, classification report, and skops model.
- Best run is tagged `best_run=true`. Optional registry name via `MLFLOW_REGISTER_MODEL_NAME`.

## Threshold / Uncertainty Policy
- `thresholds.py` applies `min_conf` and `min_margin` to route low-certainty outputs to `Potential`.
- Presets in `configs/thresholds.yaml` (high_precision / high_recall).
- API/Streamlit responses include `policy_reason`, `confidence`, and per-class probabilities.

## Serving
- FastAPI endpoints: `/health`, `/version`, `/predict`, `/batch_predict`, `/reload_model`.
- Model loads from `models/` by default; optional MLflow artifact path via config.
- Streamlit UI calls the API, shows probabilities, policy reason, and supports CSV batch scoring.

## Data & Preprocessing
- Uses `preprocess_text.py` (mmdt-tokenizer) for cleaning/tokenization.
- Processed dataset expected at `data/processed/preprocess_mmdt_tokenizer.xlsx`.
- Data versioning recommended via DVC; hashes logged to MLflow.

## CI/CD and Ops (scaffolding)
- Tests: `uv run pytest`; lint: `ruff`, `black --check`; types: `mypy` (add later).
- Dockerfile.api + docker-compose (mlflow optional) for local demo.
- Add Trivy image scan and registry promotion gates as follow-up.

## Monitoring & Guardrails (roadmap)
- Prometheus/Grafana for latency/error rate; whylogs/evidently for drift.
- Input guardrails: max text length, optional PII/profanity scrub.
- Batch scoring with drift reports saved to `reports/` and logged to MLflow.
